1.
Power BI is a Microsoft business analytics tool used to visualize data and share insights.
Main components:

Power BI Desktop – for data modeling and report creation.
Power BI Service – for publishing and sharing reports online.
Power BI Mobile – for accessing dashboards on mobile devices.

2. Name two business use cases for Power BI dashboards.

Sales performance tracking – analyzing revenue by region or product.
Customer behavior analysis – monitoring purchase trends or satisfaction.

3. How do you download and install Power BI Desktop?

Go to the Microsoft Power BI official website or Microsoft Store.
Click Download Power BI Desktop.
Run the installer and follow setup instructions.

4. What is the difference between Power BI Desktop and Power BI Service?
Feature	Power BI Desktop	Power BI Service
Purpose	Build reports	Share and view reports
Location	Installed on PC	Cloud-based
Use	Data modeling	Collaboration & publishing

5. What file extension does a Power BI project use?
.pbix

6. Explain the role of Power Query in Power BI.
Power Query is the data preparation tool in Power BI. It allows users to import, clean, transform, and combine data before loading it into reports.

7. Why would a business prefer Power BI over Excel for reporting?
Interactive dashboards instead of static sheets.
Real-time data refresh.
Easier data sharing and visualization.

8. Describe one limitation of the free version of Power BI.
Free users cannot share dashboards or reports with others through the Power BI Service.

9. What is a "published report" in Power BI Service?
A published report is a report created in Power BI Desktop and uploaded to the Power BI Service to share with others or embed in dashboards.

10. How does Power BI Mobile enhance accessibility?
It allows users to view and interact with dashboards on smartphones or tablets, ensuring real-time insights anytime, anywhere.

11. Compare Power BI with Tableau—pros and cons.
Aspect	Power BI	Tableau
Cost	More affordable	More expensive
Integration	Strong with Microsoft products	Broad data source support
Ease of use	Easier for beginners	More advanced visualization flexibility
Speed	Fast for moderate data	Better for very large datasets

12. Explain how Power BI integrates with Azure services.

Power BI connects to Azure SQL Database, Azure Data Lake, Azure Synapse Analytics, and others for seamless cloud-based data analytics and machine learning integration.

13. What are "gateways" in Power BI, and when are they needed?

Gateways connect Power BI Service (cloud) with on-premises data sources.
They’re needed when data is stored locally but dashboards require automatic refresh in the cloud.

14. How would you convince a company to adopt Power BI? (ROI argument)
Power BI provides a high return on investment by:

Reducing manual reporting time.
Improving decision-making with real-time insights.
Offering low-cost licenses compared to other BI tools.

15. What security features does Power BI offer for sensitive data?

Row-Level Security (RLS)
Data encryption (in transit and at rest)

Microsoft compliance standards (GDPR, ISO)

Role-based access control
